definition.value: Any herbicide composed of urea or substituted urea substructure.
An herbicide which contains a chemically reactive phosphate ester side chain.
An herbicide which has a benzene ring that contains a cyanide grouping.
A rodenticide which contains one or more active ingredients and when consumed by rodents results in the inability to produce essential blood-clotting factors.

A methylcatechol that is benzene substituted by hydroxy, hydroxy, (3E)-penta-1,3-dien-1-yl, methyl and methoxy groups at positions 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5, respectively. It is an iron(III)-reducing natural product isolated from the ascomycota Trichoderma harzianum.
